We may now readily complete the proof of Proposition A, as follows. In the first place, if \(T=\,T^{\prime}\), then the claim, applied to the last box \((s,\,a_{s})\) of \(F_{s}\), shows that \(\sigma=I\). On the other hand, if \(T\neq T^{\prime}\), pick the \(<_{t}\) earliest box \((i,j)\) of \(F_{s}\) for which \(T\) and \(T^{\prime}\) differ; the claim then shows that \(T(i,j)\,<\,T^{\prime}(i,j)\) whence \(T\,<_{p}\,T^{\prime}\). Q.E.D.

